wikipedia_page.main: George Shuldham Hume (4 March 1800 – 25 November 1872) was an English first-class cricketer. He is recorded as a batsman for Cambridge University in two matches in 1821, totalling 165 runs with a highest score of 97 not out.Hume was educated at Eton and King's College, Cambridge. After graduating he became a Church of England priest and was vicar of Melksham (with Seend, Erlestoke and Shaw) from 1825 until his death.
